Definition.WordDefinition: Objectionable \Ob*jec"tion*a*ble\, a. Liable to objection; likely to be objected to or disapproved of; offensive; as, objectionable words. -- {Ob*jec"tion*a*bly}, adv. [1913 Webster]

objectionable adj 1: causing disapproval or protest; "a vulgar and objectionable person" [syn: {obnoxious}, {unpleasant}] 2: liable to objection or debate; used of something one might take exception to; "a thoroughly unpleasant highly exceptionable piece of writing"; "found the politician's views objectionable" [syn: {exceptionable}]
